  <body>
      <sec>
          <title>The future</title>
          <p>
              We think that the way ahead must embrace both longer mean consultation times and
              more flexibility. To reduced levels of stress.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B20">20</xref>
              They will also find it easier to develop further the care of chronic disease.
          </p>
          <p>
              Which is still envied in other developed
              countries.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B21">21</xref> Access needs to be simple and
              overmedicalisation need to be exploited.
          </p>
          <p>There should be far more managerial emphasis on helping patients to interact with
              their chosen practitioner<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B22">22</xref>; such a
              programme has been described.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B23">23</xref>
              There is a place for both.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B2">2</xref> Access without
              prior appointment is a valued feature.
          </p>
      </sec>
